

**********terraform install********

sudo yum install -y yum-utils
sudo yum-config-manager --add-repo https://rpm.releases.hashicorp.com/AmazonLinux/hashicorp.repo
sudo yum -y install terraform





1. AWS Credentials (Authentication)
Terraform needs permission to access your AWS account. You do not write these directly in the Terraform files (for security reasons). Instead, configure them in your terminal before running Terraform:

Option A: Using the AWS CLI (Recommended) Open your command prompt/terminal and run:

aws configure
It will prompt you to enter:

AWS Access Key ID    
AWS Secret Access Key    
Default region name (e.g., us-east-1)
Option B: Environment Variables If you don't have the AWS CLI, set these variables in your terminal session:

cofigure aws cli 
curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"
unzip awscliv2.zip
sudo ./aws/install

aws configure

$env:AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=   
$env:AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=  




2. General Settings in 
terraform.tfvars
Open your 
terraform.tfvars
 file to adjust the following options:

AWS Region (aws_region): Sets where your infrastructure will be built.

hcl

******change resion in a vpc variable file******************
aws_region = "us-east-1"  # Change to your preferred region (e.g., us-west-2, ap-south-1)
SSH Key Pair (key_name): If you want to SSH/connect to the EC2 instances for testing:

Go to your AWS Console -> EC2 -> Key Pairs and check your key pair name (or create a new one).
Uncomment and add its name in terraform.tfvars:
hcl


key_name = "my-existing-aws-key"


3. Custom Settings (Optional)
If you want to customize your setup further:

Custom AMI (ami_id): By default, Terraform dynamically searches for the latest official Amazon Linux 2 image. If you prefer to manually supply an AMI ID, uncomment it in terraform.tfvars:

hcl


ami_id = "ami-0c7217cdde317cfec"  # Replace with your specific AMI ID
Instance Type (instance_type): If you need larger instances than t2.micro (which is AWS Free-Tier eligible):

hcl


instance_type = "t3.micro"
